Prevalence:</font></b></p><p><font style="font-size: 14px;">From adult population in England identify the population of people living with MASLD via prevalence estimates.</font></p><p><b><font style="font-size: 14px;">2. Sub-Population Prevalence:</font></b></p><p><font style="font-size: 14px;">Within the MASLD population determine the population living with MASH.</font></p><p><b><font style="font-size: 14px;">3. Fibrosis Stage:</font></b></p><p><font style="font-size: 14px;">Establish the proportion of MASH patients with each Fibrosis score.</font></p><p><b><font style="font-size: 14px;">4. Comorbidities receiving treatment (Obesity and Diabetes):</font></b></p><p><font style="font-size: 14px;">Determine the proportion of patients in each sub-group that overlap with Obesity and Type 2 Diabetes. Establish the proportion of these patients potentially receiving treatments that overlap/preclude emergent treatments.</font></p><p><span style="font-size: 14px;"><b>5.
